<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-10-29T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-10-29T12:00:00-05:00" n="785" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d785">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72114/2988</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PWH1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Page</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-10-29T12:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">October 29, 1917, 12
                                noon</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>5677. The following, strictly confidential, received from Copenhagen
                            today:</p>
                        <p>[Here follows text of telegram No. 1482 of October 25, <hi rend="italic">supra.</hi>]</p>
                        <p>Please take up matter with Minister of Foreign Affairs orally and
                            ascertain his views. Also what steps, if any, British Government
                            contemplates taking. Similar instructions telegraphed Ambassador at
                                Paris.<note n="2" xml:id="d785fn2">Telegram No. 2748 of Oct. 29.
                                (Same file number as above.)</note> Text furnished Petrograd<note n="3" xml:id="d785fn3">Telegram No. 1805 of Oct. 29. (Same file
                                number as above.)</note> to report as to authenticity without making
                            any representations whatever.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>